This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new approach for knowledge distillation, which is a popular technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper conducts experiments on image classification and object detection tasks, which are common applications of machine learning. The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) as it uses image datasets and evaluates the performance of the proposed method on image-related tasks. The paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as knowledge distillation is a technique that can be applied to various AI-related tasks, and the paper does not limit its scope to computer vision. Finally, the paper may involve neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a method for transferring knowledge between neural networks.
